Countries to look into IMF resource boost: Van Rompuy
2011-11-04 13:52:54 GMT
CANNES, France, Nov. 4 (Xinhua) -- G20 Finance ministers will look into ways to boost the amount of money available to the International Monetary Fund (IMF), European Council President Herman Van Rompuy said here on Friday."We wanted more lending capacity, more resources, available for the International Monetary Fund," Van Rompuy told a news conference Friday noon towards the end of the two-day G20 summit in the French resort city of Cannes."We have different options…One of the options is to set up… some kind of trust fund, enhancing the resources of the IMF,” Van Rompuy said, adding that the boost would not only benefit Europe but also the world community.
